    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2\"><style>[data-colorid=z89ykq0wk0]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=z89ykq0wk0]{color:#004eb3}[data-colorid=cqdkaiu1rp]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=cqdkaiu1rp]{color:#004eb3}</style>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218309&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/600113153/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218309&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"611\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"600113166\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"600113153\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"4\" data-media-id=\"7b13088b-8e9a-4e4a-924d-10ee2f63f546\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218309&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=611 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218309&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362 1x\" /></span><p>Get started with MaterialX Lama, a production-ready material layering system developed by Industrial Light &amp; Magic.</p><hr /><h3 id=\"R.F.-Materials-Lama-LamaBasics\"><span data-colorid=\"cqdkaiu1rp\">Lama Basics</span></h3><p /><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"47f8ac94-0910-4fca-a6d8-4e6f8f89ab36\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-2137565589\"><div id=\"expander-control-2137565589\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Overview</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-2137565589\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"70d3142d-12d3-4b73-bce4-e7b8d76dff05\" data-macro-id=\"6a52d715390abd4ad9654837db35b6338a03c00d31400f175cd479edabb733cf\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/568462499\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>This intro will give you an overview of the forthcoming lessons on Industrial Light &amp; Magic's cutting-edge layered material system.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"9347db02-48bd-4986-b3cf-2c9181f298e5\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1974890350\"><div id=\"expander-control-1974890350\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Surface</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1974890350\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"c3bbb305-0279-45d8-bbcc-05bd858fb5e2\" data-macro-id=\"1f7ba9f8e5496db121ffa53bb50daee5d5d30de08d3c0c05f344bab0213bba60\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/604805367\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson, we'll be taking a first look at the MaterialX Lama Surface node and how it should be used as the base of all your Lama layered materials.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"fb88c867-1ab5-4160-b1bb-8acad0349fd1\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1926121081\"><div id=\"expander-control-1926121081\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Surface - 2 Sided</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1926121081\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"85fc92b9-6da1-4101-b8c1-be4b29fea3b9\" data-macro-id=\"77c95a70a6c87019a6cd9c14a0ef0ef0006c7ea3ed2fdc0502f4993a945f286f\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/619820150\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Expanding on the first lesson, we'll learn to create two-sided Lama layered materials.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"66f4fd4d-dbac-4db3-a834-781c4faa0d4e\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1387045658\"><div id=\"expander-control-1387045658\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Diffuse</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1387045658\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"1f7efea4-3efe-4e82-8491-efe0248e9b1a\" data-macro-id=\"71340dbc4ac04de9e71ebe79d0534a6e1819c4f9f9e0a748905f00147bb4f735\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/604773734\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Learn how to use this fundamental building block for Lama material networks.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"7c04f303-5e38-4815-b2cc-ac772675115d\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-725123606\"><div id=\"expander-control-725123606\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Dielectric</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-725123606\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"10e9ab9b-f770-4b43-a3a6-c7b074e677cc\" data-macro-id=\"1fbe1cbdc1cf603c0226f0ca40259f126f7299bd97d21917e66b91ddeb8269fd\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/637863207\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Create layer coatings, glass, plastics, diamonds, and other materials using Lama Dielectric.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"61933b77-cc7b-41fd-8e60-2abcaa1ea1f5\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-292309587\"><div id=\"expander-control-292309587\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Emission</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-292309587\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"47d92a70-8131-4204-91b8-6a9f8e91e2a0\" data-macro-id=\"1f7df482f5611b879601323186f6a14b53411ead0c7fca37b6ce5ee7e0845ffc\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/604779917\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Learn the basics of using material emission with MaterialX Lama.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"72838cc5-44f3-4756-9956-d3b6dbd5805e\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-306239320\"><div id=\"expander-control-306239320\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Sheen</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-306239320\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"482e3c93-423f-4a9a-a6d6-c46f36d5c5f6\" data-macro-id=\"6a255210d9ed102c032d9bfcf76642fd03e05148d2a10282544fafa71e9b0ae9\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/604783317\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>This lesson will introduce you to the LamaSheen node, typically used to simulate cloth, velvet, or layers of dust.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"7338fa35-6312-487a-b86c-87b17cf96b33\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-2004215115\"><div id=\"expander-control-2004215115\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Conductor</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-2004215115\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"863361c7-f511-44a5-a46e-fc9d5fa2ef2f\" data-macro-id=\"47be7fc65775bafcc99949927139c01d45b48af68c79cc78ddf1b65ace542f5b\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/619793054\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson you'll learn the fundamentals of the Lama Conductor node and how it can be used to create beautiful and realistic metals.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"33fbce3c-e3ad-4958-b5e4-1d32df19e63c\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1798260936\"><div id=\"expander-control-1798260936\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama SSS</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1798260936\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"d29fdf29-81c1-4999-b92c-e4e01c8f08bd\" data-macro-id=\"56bf683b375e4fe3e70007dd479d97ce0d700101311710c10b7e7c864bc860ba\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/604787559\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson, you'll learn the basics of the LamaSSS and LamaTriColor nodes for simulating subsurface scattering, an effect needed for candles, chocolate, skin, and other surfaces that scatter light.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"2e4cddb4-9a89-4779-888e-6014f6830089\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1467647373\"><div id=\"expander-control-1467647373\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Lama Layer</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1467647373\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"64508c76-05be-43d9-bda2-95256a7d86b1\" data-macro-id=\"70da2b8b8b3e7b112abe8a3b06b4add77e96fb56b98ce97b2202555c0ab048b1\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/619829289\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson you'll learn how to use the Lama Layer node as the building blocks to your Material X Lama materials.</p></div></div><p /><hr /><h3 id=\"R.F.-Materials-Lama-NextSteps\"><span data-colorid=\"z89ykq0wk0\">Next Steps</span></h3><p>Ready for the next step in your RenderMan Fundamentals learning path?</p><p>Let&rsquo;s move on to learning the beautiful shaders that ship with RenderMan and are used by Pixar Animation Studios themselves.</p><p /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-equal\" data-layout=\"two-equal\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RU/pages/599523329/R.F.+-+Materials+-+PxrSurface\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523329\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" alt=\"previousLesson.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218310&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/600113153/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218310&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"67\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"600113169\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"previousLesson.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"600113153\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"4\" data-media-id=\"193b45dd-bb86-4575-ac39-3e218d6de88d\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218310&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=67 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218310&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46 1x\" /></span></a><p /></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RU/pages/599523361/R.F.+-+Patterns\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523361\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-right-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-right\" alt=\"nextLesson.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/600113153/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"67\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"600113172\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"nextLesson.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"600113153\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"4\" data-media-id=\"2eca1945-71f1-4d59-85b9-fc75df350647\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=67 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/600113153/nextLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757846218702&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46 1x\" /></span></a><p /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<hr /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png\" width=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/downloa